
1.) Create a directory "code" in the root directory and change to 
    that directory.
 
    mkdir code
    cd code

2.) Download the latest stable version of LAMMPS from the LAMMPS homepage and 
    extract it. Here we use the version 30Jul16. If you use a different version, just use your version number for the commands     below.

    wget http://lammps.sandia.gov/tars/lammps-30Jul16.tar.gz
    tar -xvf lammps-30Jul16.tar.gz

3.) Change to the src directory.

    cd lammps-30Jul16/src/

4.) Install the package DIPOLE.

    make yes-dipole yes-rigid yes-python yes-opt

5.) Update some of the old source files and add the new ones.

    cp ../../../src/*.h ../../../src/*.cpp .

6.) Compile LAMMPS (in parallel on four cores) with 

    make -j4 mpi
    
    for the parallel version or with
    
    make serial
    
    for the serial version.
    

The current directory should now contain an executable lmp_mpi or lmp_serial depending on which command you used for the compilation. 

You should now be able to run LAMMPS with the input scripts provided. For example, if you want to run sim/in.membrane, first 
change the directory and then execute LAMMPS with the input file.

    cd ../../../sim
    mpirun -np 4 ../code/lammps-30Jul16/src/lmp_mpi -in in.membrane

    or
   
    ../code/lammps-30Jul16/src/lmp_serial -in in.membrane


(Your simulation should be running now.)
